I really doubt there's any actual processor speed change here, as the CPU has a fixed clock and there is no way to change that in software. It's much more likely that this is just a bug, as Memblers said. I don't think it's due to pooling $2002 though, since missing VBlanks would actually make the game slower... We'd have to take a look at that part of the game while it's running to have a better idea, though. But that game does not seem very fun, as the angry Nintendo nerd advised. =D<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Oct 25, 2006 6:36 am</p><hr />
